# Pioneer Agent CODEOWNERS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Replace @OWNER with your GitHub username (or team handle) during onboarding.
# The Pioneer wizard does this automatically when generating a new agent
# repo from the template.
#
# Goal: enforce the three-tier model from SOUL.md / MEMORY_POLICY.md.
#   - Governed files: require owner review; block agent self-edits.
#   - PR-gated files: open for agent proposals, owner merges.
#   - Ephemeral files: gitignored, not visible to this system.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Default — everything requires owner review.
*                          @OWNER

# Governance tier — owner ONLY. Agent-authored PRs touching these files
# must be rejected at review.
/workspace/SOUL.md            @OWNER
/workspace/MEMORY_POLICY.md   @OWNER
/.github/CODEOWNERS           @OWNER
/.github/workflows/           @OWNER

# PR-gated tier — agents may propose, owner merges. No special codeowners
# beyond the default, but naming them keeps intent explicit.
# /workspace/IDENTITY.json    @OWNER
# /workspace/AGENT_BRIEFING.md @OWNER
# /tools.d/                   @OWNER
# /skills/                    @OWNER
# /workspace/notes/           @OWNER
